Package: survRho
Type: Package
Title: Closed-Form Bounds on the Required Accrual Rate Multiplier for
    Unequal Randomization in Survival Trials
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Gosuke", "Homma", email = "my.name.is.gosuke@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Sho", "Komukai", role = "aut"))
Maintainer: Gosuke Homma <my.name.is.gosuke@gmail.com>
Description: Provides closed-form expressions and analytical bounds for the
    accrual rate multiplier rho* that preserves the overall trial duration
    when switching from 1:1 to r:1 randomization in time-to-event clinical
    trials. The package implements the universal lower bound, the tight
    lower bound, and the upper bound on rho* derived under the
    Lachin-Foulkes (1986) sample size framework with Schoenfeld's (1981)
    required number of events, and provides utilities for computing trial
    duration, relative efficiency, and the numerical value of rho* via
    root-finding. The methodology is described in Homma and Komukai (20XX)
    "When Does Unequal Randomization Shorten Survival Trials? Closed-Form
    Bounds on the Required Accrual Rate".
